title: For Sale:  Hi-Point .45
postcontent:
Up for sale is my first handgun. The Hi-Point .45. I had originally bought this gun as a home defense weapon. I was living in an apartment in a shady part of town and I was on a budget. Naturally, Hi-Point was my only choice. Now, for the good, the bad, and the ugly. I will rate each on a 1-10 scale for each point. 
First the bad...the gun is a mild nuisance to take apart. You have to take a pin out of the middle to take down. There will be no taking it down at the range without a small hammer and punch. Not the big of deal to me, I just thought I would mention it. Rating (5). 
Second the good...if you are on a budget and want .45 stopping power, this is the gun for you!! (10). I have shot this gun out to 50 yards hitting 4 inch plate steel no problem!! Accuracy rating (10)!! 
And finally, the ugly. Well...that's just it....the gun is ugly. There is no denying it. It is heavy, clunky, and ugly. But the good thing is that if you run out of ammo you can bludgeon someone to death with 2 or 3 blows tops. Let's be honest, you're on a budget, you want something with a better reputation than a Jennings, and you want .45 stopping power. I have loved this gun for its stopping power and accuracy. And you know what....every time I have taken it to the range, everyone asks about, everyone wants to shoot it and everyone is amazed at how accurate it is! So remember, if you are on a budget, if you want the most reliable handgun in that price range, and you want accuracy and stopping power, this is the gun for you. Text me at REDACTED. Or email me at REDACTED

P.S. Comes with everything in picture. Gun, one mag, trigger lock and tool, half box of ammo
 Check budsgunshop.com to confirm new price. Also I have less than 100 rounds through the gun. Gun brand new is $171. Leg holster was $25. So the price for everything new was just under $200. I am letting it all go for $125. The picture of the paper target is me shooting the .45 at 30 yards!!! All rounds through the head! Pretty impressive if you ask me.

As a side note I also have a Hi-Point C-9. A great, compact gun chambered in 9mm. That package comes with gun, one mag, trigger lock and locking tool, hip holster. Brand new gun $175. Hip holster $20. Total package brand new is just under $200. I will let this package go for $125 also. 

You can have both for $225.
